  "text": "In [CITATION_1] , the nonfreeness of a density operator ∆ on the many-fermion Fock space was defined to be the entropy of ∆ relative to the unique free state with the same 1-matrix as ∆, and it was shown there that this relative entropy is given by formula (3) above. In this article, we shall define nonfreeness for bosonic states analogously, and we shall show that it is given by formula (4) above.",
